item.title: Base Metals Rise, Gold Slips Amid Choppy Macro Sentiment
item.description: Base-metal prices were rising while gold fell in early London trade, with strong jobs data in the U.S. likely to cement further rate hikes this year, a headwind for gold as of late, against more positive economic data coming from China.

item.title: Stock Futures Firmer as House Approves Debt-Ceiling Deal
item.description: Stock futures edged higher after the House passed the debt-ceiling bill, which pairs spending cuts with suspension of the U.S. borrowing limit until January 2025. It now heads to the Senate.

item.title: Dollar Stalls as Fed Officials Talk of Skipping June Rate Rise
item.description: The dollar stalled in early European trading, pulling away from recent highs, after two Fed officials suggested the central bank could opt to keep interest rates steady in June and raise them in July instead.

item.title: Oil Gains After China's Manufacturing PMI Rises
item.description: Oil prices edged higher in Europe as Chinese data pointed to expanding factory activity, and as expectations for an OPEC+ meeting this weekend were also fluctuating, with most analysts taking the view it will hold off from adjusting production levels for now.

item.title: S&P Seen as Unlikely to Change France's Rating, Outlook on Friday
item.description: France is expected to retain both its ‘AA’ rating and negative outlook when S&P reviews the country’s rating on Friday, Citi said, which should mean limited market impact from the decision.

item.title: SAS Backs Guidance on Demand Momentum
item.description: SAS reported an unchanged second quarter net loss, as higher revenue was offset by increased fuel prices and other costs, and reiterated its full-year financial targets.

item.title: Drones Hit Russian Oil Refineries as Moscow Shores Up Front Line
item.description: Such attacks come as Russia loses the initiative in the conflict, say Western officials, with Moscow increasingly reacting to Ukrainian offensives that are setting the agenda on the battlefield.

item.title: Remy Cointreau Remains Cautious on Outlook
item.description: Remy Cointreau reported a full-year operating profit of €430 million, above expectations, but said it still expects little growth in margins or sales in fiscal 2024, as U.S. consumption drops from recent highs.

item.title: A Visual Breakdown of America's Stagnating Number of Births
item.description: Births stayed flat in 2022, with numbers down among younger women, new federal figures show.
